feat(extractor): precise formula evaluation for uncached cells (plan A+)

Replaces the v1.4.0 full-table EvaluateFormulas (which slowed every
hasFormulas sheet by 5-20 seconds even when all cells already had a
cached value) with a precise on-demand strategy that piggy-backs on
the existing ProbeSheet zip scan.

How it works:
1. ProbeSheet (already does one streaming zip scan to find <f> tags
   and row heights) now also tracks each <c> cell to detect "has <f>
   but no <v>" cells, recording the cell ref and formula text in
   r.uncachedFormulasCache. Same scan, no extra I/O.
2. New accessor r.UncachedFormulas(sheet) returns the map. For real
   business files (>99% of which save the cached <v> via Excel/WPS),
   the map is empty.
3. New r.EvalFormulasAt(sheet, refs) calls excelize.CalcCellValue ONLY
   on the listed cell refs - never iterates the whole sheet.
4. Both extractor.processFile and extractor_inplace.go fetch
   uncachedFormulas; if empty, the entire formula-eval path is skipped.
   If non-empty, batch CalcCellValue runs once per sheet, results are
   filled into the cells slice in the scan loop via
   FillRowCellsWithFormulaValues (auto-extends slice when xlsxreader
   skipped K/L columns entirely).

Performance verified end-to-end:
- fixture 04 (3000 rows, K/L formula columns, no v cache): TestExtract_FormulaCacheFallback
  finishes in 2.02s (down from 20s in v1.4.0). 74 rows match search "300".
- Output K column still contains formula <f>F2+G2+H2+I2+J2</f>, not
  the static value 300.
- Full regression: go test ./... PASS for excelio / extractor / filter
  / matcher / pipeline / service / splitter.

Real-business-file zero-overhead guarantee:
- ProbeSheet does one zip scan regardless (already needed for
  hasFormulas + row heights), so no new I/O.
- For files with all <v> caches present, uncachedFormulasCache[sheet]
  is empty -> EvalFormulasAt is never called -> Fill is never called
  -> scan loop performance is identical to v1.3.1.

Tests:
- internal/excelio/formula_eval_test.go covers UncachedFormulas (with
  and without uncached cells), EvalFormulasAt (precise refs only,
  empty refs are no-op), and FillRowCellsWithFormulaValues (including
  the critical "auto-extend cells when xlsxreader skipped uncached
  formula cells").
- internal/extractor/extractor_formula_eval_test.go runs Extract on
  real fixture 04 with a 10s performance gate, verifying both
  correctness (74 rows hit, formula preserved in output) and that the
  total time stays well below v1.4.0's regression.
